	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100640059848667><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=4666&mid=100640059848667>CHA IS CHECKED!!</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=4666&mid=100640059848667#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=112076><span id= >Dqual</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>21 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 21st 10:43 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>People do not understand the attributes in EQ at all!<br><br>CHA is not CHARM, but CHARISMA.<br>Charisma is how convincing you are, both in evil and good ways, so high CHA will improve both fear and charm, which is both checked against CHA.<br><br>CHA is the attribute the caster needs to increase to get a succesfull hit and MR is the attribute the target needs to improve the chances of a resist.<br>This is exactly like a melee that has to increase his melee skills in that particulat weapontype he is using to get a hit and the target needs to get AGI up to dodge and AC to take less damage.<br>(DEX for a melee only affect the chance melee skill increase and special attacks, like BS, crippling and weapon procs)<br><br>Its although true that CHA do not have much effect in the normal game, since the level difference is more important.<br>CHA will however be usefull when trying to fear or charm mobs that are higher in level than the caster.<br>This is normally only done by bards and enchanters in raid situations, and the necro's fear is normally not wanted in these situations, so the necro goes for HP/mana/resist gear instead.<br><br>Dqual<br>52 Necro<br>Antonious Bayle<br>May you all go to hell!!!<br>(My kind of heaven) :)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
